Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve any large cauliflower florets and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{1}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop them onto a piece of #foil{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drizzle the @balsamic glaze{12} over the tomatoes, then fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel.

Pop the tomato parcel onto a baking tray and roast on the bottom shelf of your oven until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

While everything roasts, peel and grate the @garlic clove{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @harissa paste{50} and half the garlic. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the lentils, @vegetable stock paste{10} and @water for the lentils{100}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto another baking tray, cut-side up.

Spread over the remaining garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil for the garlic bread{1}.

Bake the garlic bread on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the garlic ciabatta bakes, crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50} into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @dill{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

When everything's ready, stir the @sumac{1} and half the dill into the lentils. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the roasted tomatoes, including the juices from the parcel.

Top with the roasted cauliflower, Greek style salad cheese and remaining dill.

Cut the garlic ciabatta diagonally into triangles and serve alongside.

Enjoy!